+From d8d0379f9221f3056e0ea52d807828541d6dc4ae Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
+From: raarion <raarion@users.noreply.github.com>
+Date: Wed, 24 Jun 2026 03:00:08 +0000
+Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat:=20v0.7.0=20=E2=80=94=20Data=20Fetching=20?=
+ =?UTF-8?q?&=20Event=20Modifiers?=
+MIME-Version: 1.0
+Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
+Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit
+
+FASE 2 dari blueprint: memperkuat Ambil dari + event modifiers.
+Prinsip: TIDAK ada keyword async/await di DSL — compiler menyembunyikannya.
+
+### 2.1a Compiler: .then() chains → async/await IIFE
+- visitAmbilLuarStatement rewritten: emit async IIFE dengan try/catch/finally
+- Developer menulis 'Ambil dari URL:', compiler emit async/await di balik layar
+- Proper HTTP status check: if (!__response.ok) throw Error
+- Default error handler jika tidak ada branch gagal
+
+### 2.1b Parser: Ambil dari URL: dengan options + branches
+- Parser sekarang mendeteksi 'Ambil dari URL:' (AmbilLuar) vs 'ambil nilai dari elemen' (AmbilDom)
+- Options: metode/method, isi/body, header/headers, mode, kredensial/credentials
+- Branches: berhasil/success, gagal/error, selalu/always/finally
+- Body option auto-wrapped dengan JSON.stringify
+- Indonesian option names mapped ke fetch API (metode→method, isi→body)
+
+### 2.1c Compiler: request cancellation di SPA mode
+- AbortController auto-generated saat SPA mode aktif
+- Signal di-pass ke fetch options
+- Controller.abort() di-push ke __cleanupFns (cleanup saat unmount)
+- AbortError di-ignore di catch block (request cancelled = expected)
+
+### 2.2 Event Modifiers (.cegah, .prevent, .hentikan, .stop, .sekali, .once)
+- Lexer: regex event line updated untuk match on_event.modifier = expr
+- Parser: modifiers di-extract dari event name string (on_klik.cegah → event=diklik, modifiers=[cegah])
+- Compiler: emit event.preventDefault() / event.stopPropagation() berdasarkan modifiers
+- Backward compat: on_disubmit tanpa modifier tetap auto-preventDefault
+
+### Fixes
+- Added on_dikirim event alias (dikirim → submit)
+- Added __data, __error, __response to resolver JS_GLOBALS whitelist
+- 22 new tests in tests/v0.7-data-fetching.test.js
+- 328 tests passing (306 existing + 22 new), 0 failed
